\section{Current Work}

\subsection{Introduction}
\begin{frame}{Introduction}
As we want to improve our accuracy, we begin to study the $XYZ$ data, and we choose four energy points, namely $4230$, $4260$, $4360$ and $4420$.\\
        and the process is\\
\begin{center}
$e^+e^-\to\pi^+\pi^-h_c$\\
$h_c\to\gamma\eta_c$\\
$\eta_c \to K_S^0 K \pi$\\
\end{center}
\bigskip
The idea is the same as the $\psi\prime$ analysis. \\
We establish a $\gamma\pi\pi$ list to do the analysis.\\
\begin{block}{}
\begin{itemize}
\item $3.45<m_{\pi^+\pi^-}^{recoil}<3.65 GeV$\\
\item $2.8<m_{\pi^+\pi^-\gamma}^{recoil}<3.2 GeV$
\end{itemize}
\end{block}
\end{frame}

